frclib

Class FrcPneumatic

  • java.lang.Object
    • frclib.FrcPneumatic

  • public class FrcPneumatic
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements a platform dependent pneumatic object. A pneumatic object consists of multiple pneumatic channels. Pneumatic channels can be used to control a pneumatic valve or something that simply needs some voltage to be turned on and off. For example, a 12V LED strip can be controlled by a pneumatic channel. An RGB LED strip can be controlled by 3 pneumatic channels. Therefore, this class provides methods to turn on and off multiple pneumatic channels in many different ways. It can even turn on and off the channels in a sequence of ON and OFF with different time periods and in a loop so the RGB LED strip can be blink in different colors in various blinking patterns.

      • set

        public void set(byte solMask,
                double onPeriod,
                trclib.TrcEvent event)
        This method sets the specified pneumatic channels to ON or OFF for a specified period of time and optionally signals an event when the period has expired.
        Parameters:
        solMask - specifies the bit mask of all channels. 1's specify ON channels and 0's specify OFF channels.
        onPeriod - specifies the period of time the ON channels remained ON and turn them off afterwards.
        event - specifies the event to be signaled when the ON period expires, null if none specified.

      • set

        public void set(byte solMask1,
                double period1,
                byte solMask2,
                double period2,
                boolean repeat,
                trclib.TrcEvent event)
        This method sets all pneumatic channels to the states specified by solMask1 for period1 then sets them to the states specified by solMask2 for period2. If repeat is true, the period1 and period2 patterns repeat. Otherwise, the specified event is signaled. If repeat is true, the event parameter is ignored.
        Parameters:
        solMask1 - specifies first bit mask of all channels. 1's specify ON channels and 0's specify OFF channels.
        period1 - specifies the period of time the mask 1 channels will remained in their states.
        solMask2 - specifies second bit mask of all channels. 1's specify ON channels and 0's specify OFF channels.
        period2 - specifies the period of time the mask 2 channels will remained in their states.
        repeat - specifies true if this mask1/mask2 pattern will be repeated, false otherwise.
        event - specifies the event to be signaled when period2 has expired, null if none specified. This parameter is ignored if repeat is true.

      • set

        public void set(FrcPneumatic.SolenoidAction[] actionList,
                int numActions,
                boolean repeat,
                trclib.TrcEvent event)
        This method sets the ON/OFF pattern sequence of all pneumatic channels. If repeat is true, the sequence will be repeated. Otherwise, the specified event is signaled. If repeat is true, the event parameter is ignored.
        Parameters:
        actionList - specifies the sequence of ON/OFF actions of all the pneumatic channels and their periods.
        numActions - specifies the number of valid actions in the array. The array length could be longer than numActions.
        repeat - specifies true if the sequence will be repeated, false otherwise.
        event - specifies the event to be signaled when the end of sequence has been reached, null if none specified. This parameter is ignored if repeat is true.
